<p><a name="Versions" id="Versions"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Panchatantra&amp;action=edit&amp;section=15" title="Edit section: Versions">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Versions</span></h2>
<ul>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFHertel1915">Hertel, Johannes (1915), <i><a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=-x0YAAAAYAAJ&amp;printsec=titlepage#PPR3,M1" class="external text" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=-x0YAAAAYAAJ&amp;printsec=titlepage#PPR3,M1" rel="nofollow">The Panchatantra: a collection of ancient Hindu tales in its oldest recension, the Kashmirian, entitled Tantrakhyayika</a></i>, <a href="/wiki/Harvard_University_Press" title="Harvard University Press">Harvard University Press</a><span class="printonly">, <a href="http://books.google.com/books?id=-x0YAAAAYAAJ&amp;printsec=titlepage#PPR3,M1" class="external free" title="http://books.google.com/books?id=-x0YAAAAYAAJ&amp;printsec=titlepage#PPR3,M1" rel="nofollow">http://books.google.com/books?id=-x0YAAAAYAAJ&amp;printsec=titlepage#PPR3,M1</a></span></cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Panchatantra%3A+a+collection+of+ancient+Hindu+tales+in+its+oldest+recension%2C+the+Kashmirian%2C+entitled+Tantrakhyayika&amp;rft.aulast=Hertel&amp;rft.aufirst=Johannes&amp;rft.au=Hertel%2C+Johannes&amp;rft.date=1915&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BHarvard+University+Press%5D%5D&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3D-x0YAAAAYAAJ%26printsec%3Dtitlepage%23PPR3%2CM1&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Panchatantra"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li><i>The Panchatantra Reconstructed</i> by F. Edgerton (Vol.1: Text and Critical Apparatus, Vol.2: Introduction and Translation), American Oriental Series 2-3., New Haven, Connecticut: 1924.</li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFEastwick1854">Eastwick, Edward B (transl.) (1854), <i><a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/1402186193" class="external text" title="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/1402186193" rel="nofollow">The Anvari Suhaili; or the Lights of</a> <a href="/wiki/Canopus" title="Canopus">Canopus</a> Being the Persian version of the Fables of Pilpay; or the Book Kalílah and Damnah rendered into Persian by Husain Vá'iz U'L-Káshifí</i>, Hertford: Stephen Austin, Bookseller to the East-India College<span class="printonly">, <a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/1402186193" class="external free" title="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/1402186193" rel="nofollow">http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/1402186193</a></span></cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Anvari+Suhaili%3B+or+the+Lights+of+%5B%5BCanopus%5D%5D+Being+the+Persian+version+of+the+Fables+of+Pilpay%3B+or+the+Book+Kal%C3%ADlah+and+Damnah+rendered+into+Persian+by+Husain+V%C3%A1%27iz+U%27L-K%C3%A1shif%C3%AD&amp;rft.aulast=Eastwick&amp;rft.aufirst=Edward+B+%28transl.%29&amp;rft.au=Eastwick%2C+Edward+B+%28transl.%29&amp;rft.date=1854&amp;rft.place=Hertford&amp;rft.pub=Stephen+Austin%2C+Bookseller+to+the+East-India+College&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fgp%2Fproduct%2F1402186193&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Panchatantra"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFWollaston1877">Wollaston, Arthur N. (transl.) (1877), <i>The Anwar-I-Suhaili Or Lights of <a href="/wiki/Canopus" title="Canopus">Canopus</a> Commonly Known As Kalilah And Damnah Being An Adaptation By Mulla Husain Bin Ali Waiz-Al-Kashifi of The Fables of Bidapai</i>, London: W H Allen</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Anwar-I-Suhaili+Or+Lights+of+%5B%5BCanopus%5D%5D+Commonly+Known+As+Kalilah+And+Damnah+Being+An+Adaptation+By+Mulla+Husain+Bin+Ali+Waiz-Al-Kashifi+of+The+Fables+of+Bidapai&amp;rft.aulast=Wollaston&amp;rft.aufirst=Arthur+N.+%28transl.%29&amp;rft.au=Wollaston%2C+Arthur+N.+%28transl.%29&amp;rft.date=1877&amp;rft.place=London&amp;rft.pub=W+H+Allen&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Panchatantra"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFWilkinson1930">Wilkinson (1930), <i>The Lights of Canopus described by J V S Wilkinson</i>, London: The Studio Limited</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Lights+of+Canopus+described+by+J+V+S+Wilkinson&amp;rft.aulast=Wilkinson&amp;rft.au=Wilkinson&amp;rft.date=1930&amp;rft.place=London&amp;rft.pub=The+Studio+Limited&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Panchatantra"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFFalconer1885"><a href="/wiki/Ion_Keith_Falconer" title="Ion Keith Falconer" class="mw-redirect">Falconer, Ion Keith</a> (1885), <i>Kalilah and Dimnah or The Fables of Bidpai</i>, Cambridge University Press</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Kalilah+and+Dimnah+or+The+Fables+of+Bidpai&amp;rft.aulast=Falconer&amp;rft.aufirst=Ion+Keith&amp;rft.au=Falconer%2C+Ion+Keith&amp;rft.date=1885&amp;rft.pub=Cambridge+University+Press&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Panchatantra"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span>, reprinted by Philo Press, Amsterdam 1970</li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFKnatchbull1819">Knatchbull, Rev Wyndham (1819), <i>Kalila and Dimna or The Fables of Bidpai</i>, Oxford</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Kalila+and+Dimna+or+The+Fables+of+Bidpai&amp;rft.aulast=Knatchbull&amp;rft.aufirst=Rev+Wyndham&amp;rft.au=Knatchbull%2C+Rev+Wyndham&amp;rft.date=1819&amp;rft.place=Oxford&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Panchatantra"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> (translated from Silvestre de Stacy's laborious 1816 collation of different Arabic manuscripts)</li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFWood2008">Wood, Ramsay (2008), <i><a href="http://www.amazon.co.uk/dp/0863566618/" class="external text" title="http://www.amazon.co.uk/dp/0863566618/" rel="nofollow">Kalila and Dimna, Fables of Friendship and Betrayal, Introduction by Doris Lessing</a></i>, London: Saqi<span class="printonly">, <a href="http://www.amazon.co.uk/dp/0863566618/" class="external free" title="http://www.amazon.co.uk/dp/0863566618/" rel="nofollow">http://www.amazon.co.uk/dp/0863566618/</a></span></cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Kalila+and+Dimna%2C+Fables+of+Friendship+and+Betrayal%2C+Introduction+by+Doris+Lessing&amp;rft.aulast=Wood&amp;rft.aufirst=Ramsay&amp;rft.au=Wood%2C+Ramsay&amp;rft.date=2008&amp;rft.place=London&amp;rft.pub=Saqi&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.co.uk%2Fdp%2F0863566618%2F&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Panchatantra"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
</ul>
<p><a name="English_Translations" id="English_Translations"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Panchatantra&amp;action=edit&amp;section=16" title="Edit section: English Translations">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">English Translations</span></h2>
<ul>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFRajan1993">Rajan, Chandra (transl.) (1993), <i><span lang="sa-Latn" title="International Alphabet of Sanskrit Transliteration" class="Unicode" style="white-space:normal; text-decoration: none" xml:lang="sa-Latn">Viṣṇu Śarma: The Panchatantra</span></i>, London: Penguin Books, <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780140455205" class="internal">ISBN 9780140455205</a></cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=%3Cspan+lang%3D%22sa-Latn%22+xml%3Alang%3D%22sa-Latn%22+title%3D%22International+Alphabet+of+Sanskrit+Transliteration%22++class%3D%22Unicode%22+style%3D%22white-space%3Anormal%3B+text-decoration%3A+none%22%3EVi%E1%B9%A3%E1%B9%87u+%C5%9Aarma%3A+The+Panchatantra%3C%2Fspan%3E&amp;rft.aulast=Rajan&amp;rft.aufirst=Chandra+%28transl.%29&amp;rft.au=Rajan%2C+Chandra+%28transl.%29&amp;rft.date=1993&amp;rft.place=London&amp;rft.pub=Penguin+Books&amp;rft.isbn=9780140455205&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Panchatantra"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> (reprint: 1995) (This translation is from the Jain monk Purnabhadra's 1199 CE so-called North Western Family Sanskrit text that blends and rearranges at least three earlier versions.)</li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFRyder1925"><a href="/wiki/Arthur_W._Ryder" title="Arthur W. Ryder">Ryder, Arthur W. (transl)</a> (1925), <i>The Panchatantra</i>, University of Chicago Press</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Panchatantra&amp;rft.aulast=Ryder&amp;rft.aufirst=Arthur+W.+%28transl%29&amp;rft.au=Ryder%2C+Arthur+W.+%28transl%29&amp;rft.date=1925&amp;rft.pub=University+of+Chicago+Press&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Panchatantra"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> (also republished in 1956, reprint 1964, and by Jaico Publishing House, Bombay, 1949). (also from the 1199 CE North Western Family text.)</li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFOlivelle1997">Olivelle, Patrick (transl.) (1997), <i>The Panachatantra, The Book of India's Folk Wisdom</i>, Oxford University Press, <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780192839886" class="internal">ISBN 9780192839886</a></cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Panachatantra%2C+The+Book+of+India%27s+Folk+Wisdom&amp;rft.aulast=Olivelle&amp;rft.aufirst=Patrick+%28transl.%29&amp;rft.au=Olivelle%2C+Patrick+%28transl.%29&amp;rft.date=1997&amp;rft.pub=Oxford+University+Press&amp;rft.isbn=9780192839886&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Panchatantra"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> (This translation is from the so-called Southern Family Sanskrit text, as is Franklin Edgerton's equally esteemed 1924 version.)</li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFDharma2004">Dharma, Krishna (transl.) (2004), <i>Panchatantra - A vivid retelling of India's most famous collection of fables</i>, Badger CA, USA: Torchlight Publishing, <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9781887089456" class="internal">ISBN 9781887089456</a></cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Panchatantra+-+A+vivid+retelling+of+India%27s+most+famous+collection+of+fables&amp;rft.aulast=Dharma&amp;rft.aufirst=Krishna+%28transl.%29&amp;rft.au=Dharma%2C+Krishna+%28transl.%29&amp;rft.date=2004&amp;rft.place=Badger+CA%2C+USA&amp;rft.pub=Torchlight+Publishing&amp;rft.isbn=9781887089456&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Panchatantra"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> (Accessible popular compilation derived from a Sanskrit text with reference to the aforementioned translations by Chandra Rajan and Patrick Olivelle.)</li>
<li><i>Kalila and Dimna, Fables of Friendship and Betrayal</i> by Ramsay Wood, Introduction by Doris Lessing, Postscript by Dr Christine van Ruymbeke, Saqi Books, London, 2008. <a href="http://www.amazon.co.uk/dp/0863566618/" class="external autonumber" title="http://www.amazon.co.uk/dp/0863566618/" rel="nofollow">[16]</a></li>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFOlivelle2006">Olivelle, Patrick (2006), <i>The Five Discourses on Worldly Wisdom</i>, <a href="/wiki/Clay_Sanskrit_Library" title="Clay Sanskrit Library">Clay Sanskrit Library</a></cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Five+Discourses+on+Worldly+Wisdom&amp;rft.aulast=Olivelle&amp;rft.aufirst=Patrick&amp;rft.au=Olivelle%2C+Patrick&amp;rft.date=2006&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BClay+Sanskrit+Library%5D%5D&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Panchatantra"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
</ul>
